cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with weighted automata and context-free languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a model of weighted pushdown automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper investigates the expressive power of quantitative context-free languages. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers various weight structures, including average computations. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of quantitative context-free languages assuming only finitely many values.
